{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":302775,"duration_api_ms":301606,"num_turns":3,"result":"Here's the exhaustive analysis of `schemas/`:\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n14 flat JSON Schema files — one per agent or synthesis pass. They form the **type system** of the entire ultrainit pipeline, passed to `claude -p --json-schema` to coerce LLM output into typed, parseable JSON. No subdirectories; schemas are paired 1:1 with files in `prompts/`.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n**By phase:**\n\n| Phase | Schemas |\n|---|---|\n| 1 (Gather) | `identity`, `commands`, `git-forensics`, `patterns`, `tooling`, `docs`, `security`, `structure-scout`, `module-analysis` |\n| 3 (Research) | `domain-research`, `mcp-recommendations` |\n| 4 (Synthesize) | `synthesis-docs` (Pass 1), `synthesis-tooling` (Pass 2), `synthesis-output` (merged) |\n| 5 (Validate) | reuses `synthesis-output` |\n\n**Data flow:**\n- Gather agents → `.ultrainit/findings/<agent>.json`\n- `lib/agent.sh` extracts `.structured_output` from the claude envelope with `jq`\n- Phase 4 merges Pass 1 + Pass 2 via `jq -s '.[0] * .[1]'` → `synthesis/output.json`\n- `lib/merge.sh` reads `synthesis/output.json` to write `.claude/` artifacts\n\n---\n\n## Critical Schemas\n\n**`structure-scout.json`** — Most consequential. Its `priority` enum (`high`/`medium`/`low`) directly drives which directories spawn deep-dive agents. Has a 23-value `role` enum for directory classification.\n\n**`module-analysis.json`** — Richest schema. Defines `architecture`, `key_files` (with `importance` enum), `patterns`, `conventions`, `dependencies`, `gotchas`, `domain_terms`, and the optional `skill_opportunities` array that pre-seeds skill generation.\n\n**`synthesis-tooling.json`** — Pass 2 output. Skills, hooks (with `event` enum restricted to `PreToolUse/PostToolUse/Notification/Stop`), subagents, `mcp_servers`, and `settings_hooks` wiring. Content fields are opaque strings — schema can't validate YAML frontmatter or bash syntax inside them.\n\n---\n\n## Universal Patterns\n\n1. **`additionalProperties: false` everywhere** — all 14 schemas, all nested objects. The only exception is `env` objects in MCP configs (arbitrary env var keys required).\n\n2. **Enums for all categorical fields** — never free-form strings where a controlled vocabulary exists. Enables safe `jq select(.priority == \"high\")` without defensive matching.\n\n3. **Evidence-paired findings** — `patterns.json` and `module-analysis.json` require `evidence_files[]` alongside pattern descriptions to ground LLM claims in real paths.\n\n4. **Optional arrays, never nullable** — conditional fields (e.g., `identity.packages` for monorepos only) are omitted from `required[]` but declared as arrays, so consumers can always use `jq .field[]?` safely.\n\n---\n\n## Key Gotchas\n\n- **Enum constraints aren't hard-enforced** — `claude -p` may return values outside declared enums. Downstream `jq select()` silently skips unexpected values rather than erroring.\n\n- **Angle brackets in skill descriptions break YAML parsing** — `synthesize.sh:postprocess_descriptions` strips them post-extraction. Any new synthesis prompt must repeat this constraint.\n\n- **`synthesis-output.json` is never passed to `claude -p`** — it's only the expected shape of the `jq`-merged file. No automatic validation; manual checks needed after merging.\n\n- **`mcp-recommendations.json` and `synthesis-tooling.json` MCP shapes differ** — recommendations use a nested `configuration` object; tooling flattens `command/args/env` to the top level. Direct copying between them will silently produce wrong output.\n\n- **`developer-answers.json` has no schema** — field names are a de-facto contract between `lib/ask.sh` and `lib/synthesize.sh`. Renaming any key in one requires updating all `jq` expressions in the other.\n\n- **`settings_hooks[]` ↔ `hooks[]` 1:1 correspondence is unenforced by schema** — only `validate.sh` checks this, post-extraction.\n\n- **Module findings name collision** — `module-analysis.json` is reused for all deep-dive agents, but output files use directory basenames. Two directories with the same basename (e.g., `src/api` and `lib/api`) would collide.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"5a57b0ca-71c2-4080-9b73-3e257202cde7","total_cost_usd":0.5577057,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":45088,"cache_read_input_tokens":67586,"output_tokens":6981,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":45088,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1135,"cache_read_input_tokens":40005,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5083,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5083},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":7,"outputTokens":6981,"cacheReadInputTokens":67586,"cacheCreationInputTokens":45088,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2940918,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":5589,"outputTokens":14965,"cacheReadInputTokens":1160099,"cacheCreationInputTokens":53752,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.2636139,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"module_path":"schemas/","purpose":"JSON Schema files defining the structured output contracts for every agent and synthesis pass in ultrainit. Each schema is paired with a `prompts/` file and consumed via `claude -p --json-schema` to coerce LLM output into typed, parseable JSON. Together they form the type system of the entire pipeline.","architecture":{"overview":"14 flat JSON Schema files, one per agent or synthesis pass. No subdirectories. All schemas use JSON Schema draft-07 conventions (object type, required arrays, additionalProperties: false) enforced universally. Schemas are stateless — they define output shape only, never execution logic. Three schemas use $defs for DRY reuse (notably commands.json). Two schemas (synthesis-docs.json, synthesis-tooling.json) store large markdown/bash blobs as plain strings, meaning schema validation cannot enforce internal syntax (YAML frontmatter, bash shebang, etc.) — that responsibility falls to Phase 5 validators.","subdirectories":[{"path":"schemas/","purpose":"All 14 schema files live flat in this directory, grouped conceptually by pipeline phase.","key_files":["schemas/identity.json","schemas/structure-scout.json","schemas/module-analysis.json","schemas/synthesis-docs.json","schemas/synthesis-tooling.json","schemas/synthesis-output.json"]}],"data_flow":"Phase 1 gather agents each receive a schema via --json-schema and write output to .ultrainit/findings/<agent>.json. lib/agent.sh extracts .structured_output from the claude -p JSON envelope and writes the inner object. Phase 2 (ask) has no schema — developer answers are hand-written JSON. Phase 3 research agents use domain-research.json and mcp-recommendations.json. Phase 4 synthesis passes use synthesis-docs.json (Pass 1) and synthesis-tooling.json (Pass 2); their outputs are merged with jq -s '.[0] * .[1]' into synthesis/output.json, which conforms to synthesis-output.json. Phase 5 reads synthesis/output.json and dispatches to validate-skill.sh and validate-subagent.sh for artifact-level validation that schemas cannot express."},"key_files":[{"path":"schemas/structure-scout.json","purpose":"CRITICAL. Maps all project directories to role enums (23 values) and priority levels (high/medium/low). Output directly drives which directories get deep-dive module-analysis agents in Phase 1 Stage 2. Also controls which directories get subdirectory CLAUDE.md files.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"schemas/module-analysis.json","purpose":"CRITICAL. The richest schema — defines architecture, key_files (with importance enum), patterns, conventions, dependencies, gotchas, domain_terms, and skill_opportunities. The optional skill_opportunities array pre-identifies workflows for the synthesizer. One agent instance runs per high/medium priority directory.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"schemas/synthesis-tooling.json","purpose":"Defines the output shape for Pass 2 synthesis: skills (name/description/content), hooks (filename/event enum/matcher/content), subagents, mcp_servers, and settings_hooks. Content fields store full markdown/bash as strings — schema cannot validate their internal syntax.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"schemas/synthesis-docs.json","purpose":"Pass 1 synthesis output: claude_md (full CLAUDE.md as single string) and subdirectory_claude_mds (array of {path, content}). Minimal schema — quality constraints like line count and generic-phrase detection are enforced externally by validate.sh.","importance":"critical"},{"path":"schemas/synthesis-output.json","purpose":"Final merged schema combining Pass 1 and Pass 2 fields. Used by merge.sh as the authoritative shape when writing artifacts to .claude/. Only claude_md, skills, and hooks are required; all others optional.","importance":"important"},{"path":"schemas/identity.json","purpose":"Project identity — name, description, languages (with %), frameworks (with versions), monorepo flag, packages (optional), deployment target. Required by all downstream phases as source of tech stack context.","importance":"important"},{"path":"schemas/commands.json","purpose":"All developer commands categorized into build/test/lint/format/typecheck/other. Uses $defs/command_list for DRY reuse. Each command carries scope, ci_verified bool, and source path. Drives the Quick Reference table in CLAUDE.md.","importance":"important"},{"path":"schemas/security.json","purpose":"Protected files list with path_pattern (glob), reason, and safe_alternative. Drives PreToolUse hook generation to block writes to .env, migration files, lock files, etc.","importance":"important"},{"path":"schemas/mcp-recommendations.json","purpose":"MCP server discovery output: name, package, description, relevance, and configuration (command/args/env). The env object is the only place in all 14 schemas where additionalProperties is NOT false — arbitrary env var keys are allowed.","importance":"reference"},{"path":"schemas/git-forensics.json","purpose":"Git history analysis: hotspots (top 20 files by change count), temporal coupling (top 10 co-changing file pairs), bug-fix density, ownership diffusion, recent activity by directory, commit patterns, branch naming conventions.","importance":"reference"}],"patterns":[{"name":"Universal strict mode","description":"Every schema — all 14, at every nesting level — sets additionalProperties: false. This is the single most important convention. It causes claude -p to reject any fields the LLM hallucinated beyond the declared contract. Never omit this when adding a new schema or extending an existing one.","example_files":["schemas/identity.json","schemas/module-analysis.json","schemas/synthesis-tooling.json"]},{"name":"Enum-driven categorical fields","description":"Categorical distinctions are always enums, never free-form strings. structure-scout.json has 23-value role enum and 3-value priority enum; patterns.json has a 9-value type enum; synthesis-tooling.json constrains hook events to [PreToolUse, PostToolUse, Notification, Stop]. This enables safe downstream filtering (e.g., select(.priority == \"high\")) without defensive string matching.","example_files":["schemas/structure-scout.json","schemas/patterns.json","schemas/synthesis-tooling.json"]},{"name":"$defs for repeated item shapes","description":"When the same object shape appears under multiple keys, extract it to $defs. commands.json defines command_list once and references it for all 6 categories (build, test, lint, format, typecheck, other). This is the only schema that uses $defs heavily; synthesis-tooling.json has similar repeated shapes (skill/hook/subagent) but does not consolidate them.","example_files":["schemas/commands.json"]},{"name":"Markdown/bash content as opaque strings","description":"synthesis-docs.json and synthesis-tooling.json store full document content (CLAUDE.md text, SKILL.md with YAML frontmatter, bash hook scripts) as plain JSON strings. Schema validation ends at the string boundary — structural validity of the content (valid YAML, shebang present, set -euo pipefail) must be checked externally by scripts/validate-skill.sh, scripts/validate-subagent.sh, and validate.sh hook checks.","example_files":["schemas/synthesis-docs.json","schemas/synthesis-tooling.json"]},{"name":"Optional arrays for conditional data","description":"Fields that only apply in certain contexts are excluded from the required array but declared as array types: identity.json.packages (only for monorepos), module-analysis.json.commands, module-analysis.json.skill_opportunities. All are arrays rather than nullable scalars, so consumers can always iterate safely with jq .field[]? without type-checking first.","example_files":["schemas/identity.json","schemas/module-analysis.json"]},{"name":"Importance/priority enums for triage","description":"Three schemas use tiered importance enums to drive downstream filtering decisions: structure-scout.json priority=[high,medium,low] determines which directories spawn deep-dive agents; module-analysis.json key_files importance=[critical,important,reference] drives how files are presented in CLAUDE.md; git-forensics.json uses implicit rank ordering (top-N arrays). Always use enum tiers rather than numeric scores.","example_files":["schemas/structure-scout.json","schemas/module-analysis.json"]},{"name":"Evidence-paired findings","description":"Schemas that describe code patterns require evidence_files (array of paths) alongside the pattern description. patterns.json.patterns[].evidence_files and module-analysis.json.key_files[].path enforce that LLM claims are grounded in real file references, not invented. This also enables validate-skill.sh to check that skill content references ≥3 real paths.","example_files":["schemas/patterns.json","schemas/module-analysis.json"]}],"conventions":{"naming":"Schema filenames match agent names exactly (identity.json ↔ identity agent, structure-scout.json ↔ structure-scout agent) except for three synthesis schemas (synthesis-docs.json, synthesis-tooling.json, synthesis-output.json) which map to synthesis passes, not agents. Module deep-dive outputs are named module-<dirname>.json at runtime, all sharing the same module-analysis.json schema.","imports":"Schemas are referenced by absolute path assembled at runtime in lib/gather.sh and lib/synthesize.sh via $SCRIPT_DIR/schemas/<name>.json. No bundling or $schema URI declarations. JSON Schema draft version is implicit (draft-07 conventions used but not declared).","error_handling":"Schema violations surface as claude -p exit code != 0 with error text on stdout (not stderr). lib/agent.sh captures stdout on failure and appends to the agent's .stderr log for diagnose_phase_failure. A secondary jq type check (type == \"object\" or \"array\") after extraction catches cases where claude returns a valid JSON string rather than an object.","other":["All boolean fields use JSON boolean (true/false), never strings ('yes'/'no') or integers.","All array fields are always arrays — never null or a single object — even when empty. This lets consumers use jq .field[] without defensive checks.","The env object in mcp-recommendations.json and synthesis-tooling.json MCP server entries is the only intentional additionalProperties: true — arbitrary env var key names are required.","Description fields on schema properties are prescriptive LLM instructions (e.g., 'Detailed description of the pattern including HOW to follow it'), not documentation for humans.","No $schema, $id, or version fields in any schema file. Versioning is implicit via git history."]},"dependencies":{"internal":["lib/agent.sh — consumes all gather schemas via --json-schema flag; extracts .structured_output from envelope","lib/gather.sh — references schemas/identity.json, commands.json, git-forensics.json, patterns.json, tooling.json, docs.json, security.json, structure-scout.json, module-analysis.json","lib/research.sh — references schemas/domain-research.json, mcp-recommendations.json","lib/synthesize.sh — references schemas/synthesis-docs.json, synthesis-tooling.json, synthesis-output.json; merges pass outputs","lib/validate.sh — reads synthesis/output.json (synthesis-output.json shape); dispatches to scripts/validate-skill.sh and scripts/validate-subagent.sh","lib/merge.sh — reads synthesis/output.json to write .claude/ artifacts"],"external_key":[{"name":"claude CLI (--json-schema flag)","purpose":"Structured output enforcement — passes schema to the model to coerce output shape"},{"name":"jq","purpose":"All JSON extraction, merging (jq -s '.[0] * .[1]'), and validation (type checks) after agent output is written to findings files"}]},"domain_terms":[{"term":"structured_output","meaning":"The field name inside claude -p's JSON envelope that contains the schema-conformant object. lib/agent.sh extracts this with jq '.structured_output // .result // .'"},{"term":"findings","meaning":"The inner structured object written to .ultrainit/findings/<agent>.json after extraction from the claude envelope"},{"term":"deep-dive agent","meaning":"A module-analysis agent instance spawned per directory; all share module-analysis.json schema but write to distinct finding files (module-<dirname>.json)"},{"term":"synthesis pass","meaning":"One of two large-context claude -p calls in Phase 4; Pass 1 uses synthesis-docs.json, Pass 2 uses synthesis-tooling.json"},{"term":"skill_opportunities","meaning":"Optional array in module-analysis.json where the analysis agent pre-identifies workflows worth turning into Claude Code skills; used as hints by the synthesizer"},{"term":"evidence_files","meaning":"Array of real file paths that prove a pattern exists; required in patterns.json and module-analysis.json to prevent hallucinated claims"},{"term":"settings_hooks","meaning":"Wiring entries in synthesis-tooling.json that map hook scripts to .claude/settings.json event registrations; must have 1:1 correspondence with hooks[] entries"},{"term":"matcher","meaning":"Optional field on hooks and settings_hooks that scopes a Pre/PostToolUse hook to a specific tool name (e.g., 'Write', 'Edit')"}],"gotchas":[{"issue":"Enum constraints in schemas are guidance, not hard enforcement. claude -p may return values outside declared enums (e.g., priority: 'critical' instead of 'high'). Downstream jq filters using select(.priority == 'high') silently skip unexpected values rather than erroring.","solution":"Add explicit jq validation in lib/gather.sh after structure-scout output is written: check that all priority values are in [high, medium, low] before spawning deep-dive agents. Alternatively, treat unknown priorities as 'medium'."},{"issue":"Angle brackets in skill descriptions break YAML frontmatter parsing. A description like 'Use for <adding endpoints>' causes YAML parse errors when Claude Code reads the skill file.","solution":"lib/synthesize.sh:postprocess_descriptions strips angle brackets after extraction. The synthesizer-tooling.md prompt also explicitly forbids them. When writing new synthesis prompts, repeat this constraint."},{"issue":"identity.json.packages has a conditional dependency on monorepo: true, but the schema cannot express this — packages is simply absent from the required array. Agents analyzing non-monorepos may still emit packages if confused.","solution":"Downstream consumers must check monorepo === true before iterating packages. Never assume packages is absent just because the schema doesn't require it."},{"issue":"synthesis-output.json is not actually passed to claude -p as a --json-schema. It is only the expected shape of the jq-merged file (jq -s '.[0] * .[1]' output-docs.json output-tooling.json). If either pass produces an unexpected top-level key, the merge silently wins with the second file's value.","solution":"After merging, validate the merged output against synthesis-output.json manually (e.g., via ajv or a jq type check) before passing to merge.sh."},{"issue":"The mcp-recommendations.json schema and the mcp_servers field in synthesis-tooling.json have slightly different shapes. mcp-recommendations includes relevance and a nested configuration object; synthesis-tooling.json flattens command/args/env to the top level. Copying a mcp-recommendations finding directly into synthesis output will fail.","solution":"The synthesizer prompt (synthesizer-tooling.md) must reshape MCP data. When debugging MCP config issues, check both schemas side-by-side."},{"issue":"developer-answers.json (Phase 2 output) has no schema. It is hand-assembled by lib/ask.sh and consumed verbatim in synthesis context. If ask.sh changes field names, synthesize.sh jq expressions silently return null.","solution":"Treat developer-answers.json field names (project_purpose, deployment_target, never_do, common_mistakes, additional_context) as a de-facto schema. Any change to ask.sh output keys requires updating all jq expressions in synthesize.sh."},{"issue":"settings_hooks[] entries must have a matching entry in hooks[]. The schema does not enforce this relationship — a synthesizer could generate settings_hooks without corresponding hook scripts. validate.sh checks this, but only after writing.","solution":"If adding hooks to a synthesizer prompt, always generate both the hooks[] entry (with content) and the settings_hooks[] wiring entry in the same response. Validate with: for each settings_hooks[].command basename, a matching hooks[].filename must exist."},{"issue":"module-analysis.json is reused for all deep-dive agents but output files are named module-<dirname>.json. If two directories have the same basename (e.g., src/api and lib/api), their findings files collide.","solution":"lib/gather.sh should use a sanitized full-path slug (e.g., src-api, lib-api) rather than just the basename when naming module findings files."}],"skill_opportunities":[{"name":"add-agent-schema","description":"Workflow for adding a new agent + schema pair: create the JSON schema, write the matching prompt in prompts/, register the agent call in lib/gather.sh or lib/research.sh, add a fixture in tests/fixtures/findings/, and wire a mock dispatch entry.","workflow_steps":["Create schemas/<agent-name>.json with required fields, additionalProperties: false at all levels, and appropriate enums","Create prompts/<agent-name>.md with system prompt and output contract examples","Add run_agent call in lib/gather.sh (Stage 1 or Stage 2) with correct model and allowedTools","Add a realistic fixture JSON in tests/fixtures/findings/<agent-name>.json","Add dispatch entry in tests/helpers/mock_claude.bash for the new agent name","Run make test-unit to verify agent_run.bats and gather integration tests pass"]},{"name":"validate-schema-output","description":"Given a findings JSON file, validate it against its corresponding schema using ajv or jq structural checks. Useful after agent failures or when debugging unexpected synthesis behavior.","workflow_steps":["Identify the agent name from the findings filename (e.g., identity.json → schemas/identity.json)","Run ajv validate -s schemas/<name>.json -d .ultrainit/findings/<name>.json","Report any additionalProperties violations or missing required fields","If no ajv available, use jq to spot-check required fields and enum values"]}],"commands":[{"command":"jq '.' schemas/structure-scout.json","purpose":"Inspect the most complex schema (23-value role enum, priority levels, directory mapping)"},{"command":"jq '[.properties | keys[]]' schemas/synthesis-tooling.json","purpose":"List all top-level output fields for Pass 2 synthesis"},{"command":"jq '.$defs' schemas/commands.json","purpose":"Inspect the reusable command_list definition"},{"command":"jq '[.properties.directories.items.properties.role.enum[]]' schemas/structure-scout.json","purpose":"List all valid directory role values"},{"command":"grep -l 'additionalProperties' schemas/*.json | wc -l","purpose":"Verify all schemas enforce strict mode (should equal total schema count)"}]},"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"e810288c-fade-4250-b825-c3146fd9a6cc"}
